The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | DAY I HIGHLIGHTS
                                                   DAY I HIGHLIGHTS
                      
	 Of the nine matches played at the Motera, the team that won the toss has always batted first except on one occasion when India played the West Indies on this ground in November 1983         
	 Sachin Tendulkar missed the 13th Test since he made his debut in November 1989         
	 Anil Kumble and Harbhajan Singh are playing their 50th Test together         
	 This was Sourav Gangulys 11th duck in Tests. Four of them have been against South Africa         
	 The last time India played five bowlers in a Test at home was against England in Mumbai 2005-06. England won the Test by 212 runs         
	 India had four ducks in their innings of 76, the most in all Tests against South Africa. The last time India had four ducks in an innings was versus Australia in Sydney 2007-08         
	 India were bowled out for the first time before lunch on the first day of a Test. The closest to this was when NZ dismissed India for 83 in Mohali in 1999-00. India were 42 for seven in 14 overs at lunch Start of play however was delayed due to a wet outfield         
	 This was Dale Steyns eighth 5-wicket haul in Tests. SA have won on seven occasions         
	 With the wicket of Ashwell Prince, Harbhajan Singh (267) went past Bishan Singh Bedi (266) to become the third highest wickettaker for India         
